<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Low-cost living room emulation machine]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11366&amp;p=130281#p130281"><![CDATA[
Cheapest thing that is decent is probably an original xbox. A used xbox shouldn't cost more than ~$30. It can output component video, the emulator UI's are designed for the living room, and most have an option for at least 720p video. It runs ports of popular PC emulators. It also has a controller that works well with most systems. CONS: The component video pack might cost you a bit more, and you are going to have to learn how to mod it, or find someone to mod it for you.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4680">Movax12</a> — Thu Jun 26, 2014 5:25 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
