There are a billion different computers available now that you could use for &quot;living room&quot; emulation, and I'd venture that most of them are better than a Retron 5 for playing homebrew and romhacks. HDMI output is easy to get nowadays, and there are plenty of low-cost media-centre oriented computers on the market for this kind of thing already.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Thu Jun 26, 2014 6:01 am</p><hr />
